WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
So I got this new library, it's called GreatDocs, it's for Python.

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:10.000
And basically what you do is you point it at your Python package and you create a beautiful documentation site.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Like, look at this, this front page right here, that is actually the GreatDocs site itself.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.000
And it's actually made with GreatDocs, which makes total sense when you think about it.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:23.000
And I've got some cool features, like you can make a reference page,

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:30.000
and you can show your Python API, and you can click into each one of these and get beautiful documentation.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:34.000
Let me just zoom in here to show you how beautiful it is. It looks very nice.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Not only that, you can also get information on CLIs, so you have a CLI built for your package.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.000
And you can just have it all right here, it's all documented for your users.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:46.000
They'll totally understand how to use your CLI.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:51.000
And if you've got things like an MCP server, even that will work.

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:56.000
Like, you can go into individual pages and find out all about the person's MCP server,

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:59.000
what capabilities it has, and so forth.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:02.000
And the really great thing is you can make beautiful user guide pages.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:06.000
Like, this is how you teach users to use your package.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:12.000
As you can see here, we have a huge sidebar full of interesting articles, pages,

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.000
where you can do things like have tables inside your documentation, like this.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:22.000
You can have things like page tags, videos.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:24.000
It's pretty much loaded with features.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
And that's what you want when you want to explain to users how to use your package.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:31.000
So I'm hoping that you'll check out GreatDocs.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:33.000
It's really a wonderful thing.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:40.000
As soon as you start looking at it, I'm sure you'll find ways to incorporate that with your Python package.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:42.000
Thank you.

